pr_body:
This PR adds the stm32f4 udc module, as well as a template for development and testing purposes.

Together with the previous PR #2154, these add partial usb-gadget support for stm32f40x MCUs.

To be completed, some further work needs to be accomplished:
- make DATA OUT transfers work successfully with the between the low level Cube library and the embox-gadget/udc API.
- test with the different gadgets available, and new ones(some of these will probably need some refactoring to the gadget API).
- cleanup:
  - stop using global structs, instead of passing them as pointers through the related methods.
  - fix the transfer mechanism so that it works for data_packet_size != 64bytes,
